# PiÃ±a Colada Scones

> Adapted from [this recipe](https://www.stetted.com/pina-colada-scones/)

## Scone Ingredients 

## Dry Ingredients
* 2 cups all-purpose flour
* 1/2 cup whole wheat flour
* 3/4 cup coconut flour
* 3/4 cup light brown sugar
* 2 tsp baking powder
* 2 tsp baking soda
* 2 tsp salt
* 3/4 cup shredded coconut

## Wet Ingredients
* 2 tsp vanilla extract
* 1/4 cup creme de coconut
* 3/4 cup buttermilk
* 8 tbsp unsalted butter, cut into pieces
* 1 cup crushed pineapple, drained (keep juice for glaze)
* 2 large eggs

## (Optional) Glaze Ingredients
* 1 1/2 tbsp pineapple juice
* 1 tbsp creme de coconut
* 1 1/2 cup powdered sugar
* 1/2 tsp vanilla extract
* pinch of salt

## Directions
1. Do not preheat oven yet, dough needs to chill
1  Line baking sheets with parchment paper or Silpat liner.
1. Cube the 8 tbsp butter into a bowl and refrigerate
1. In a mixer bowl, mix together all of the dry ingredients
1. With the mixer on low, add cubed butter until the chunks resemble peas
1. Mix in 1/4 cup creme de coconut, 2 eggs, 3/4 cup buttermilk, 1 cup crushed pineapple, 2 tsp vanilla just until barely incorporated
1. Heavily flour your working surface and rolling pin
1. Transfer dough to working surface and roll out to 3/4 inch thick
1. Cut dough into triangles and transfer to lined baking sheets
1. Refrigerate dough on tray until set, you can also leave it overnight


1. When you are ready to bake, preheat the oven to 400 degrees
1. Brush buttermilk onto the scones with a pastry brush
1. If you are not doing a glaze, sprinkle demerara sugar on top of the scones before baking
1. Bake for ~25 minutes, checking occasionally and rotating halfway through, until scones have risen and are a golden brown with a crispy outside


1. To make the glaze, whisk together 1 1/2 cup powdered sugar, 1 tablespoon creme de coconut, and 1 1/2 tbsp pineapple juice. Add 1/2 tsp Mexican vanilla and pinch of salt, stir until smooth and no lumps remain.
1. Drizzle over cooled scones using a fork. Let glaze set for at least 5 minutes before serving.
1. Serve immediately, as scones will lose their crunchiness overnight
